services scci stanford medicine stanford school of medicine stanford center for clinical informatics search this site only stanford medical sites ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person services the stanford center for clinical informatics supports translational research across the stanford community with a variety of services access to clinical data stride scci is the official sumc clearing house for all clinical data requests related to research the stride clinical data warehouse enables researchers to query clinical data from the electronic health records of both the stanford hospital and clinics shc and the lucile packard children's hospital lpch in a hipaa compliant manner using our self service online tools or with an in person consultation research data management solutions if you are looking to collect and manage data for a research project we have a wide range of hipaa compliant clinical research data management tools and solutions ranging from free self service solutions to paid custom software development real time research alerting researchers can be notified immediately based on specific clinical events or trends in clinical data with our real time alerting services this service has been used for patient recruitment in a number of contexts from dog bite victims entering the emergency room to monitoring in patient blood pressure and lactose levels in real time this service is for research purposes only biospecimen data management the center can provide you with sophisticated biospecimen data management tools you can also use our online search tool to search for biospecimens in several biospecimen banks supported by stride research privacy and security get in person assistance from our in house experts on biomedical research privacy and security regulatory compliance including conforming to the requirements of the hipaa privacy rule and securing phi on your computer free consultation service the center provides and encourages the use of a free in person consultation to help researchers make the best use of our tools and resources if you have specific questions or are just curious about our services please schedule a free consultation today service costs many of our services are offered free of charge to the stanford research community while others require licensing fees and or hourly salary coverage for informatics and software development labor costs please see each research service for more details or schedule a free in person consultation for more information citations and references publications resulting from the use of scci tools or consulting services should include a citation to the ctsa grant supporting stride further details including boilerplate language are available in our resources section you are here current tab 2 stanford medicine school of medicine centers & programs scci services navigation for this section services overview of services access to clinical data stride cohort discovery tool stride patient cohort data review tool stride secure workbench research data management solutions using redcap stride research data management applications comparing stride redcap and medrio software engineering and custom development real time research alerting biospecimen locator and data management research privacy and security free consultation service denotes link to stride tool site navigation about the center about us mission people what is clinical informatics contact the center services overview access to clinical data research data managementment solutions real time research alerting biospecimen data management research privacy and security free consultation service collaborations overview spotlight sumc community anesthesia cancer center orthopedics pediatrics other departments research overview stride text mining clinical vocabularies similarity matching record linkage resources informatics resources citation information stanford medicine resources stanford medicine g